    "body": "Fixes #1862\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR implements two missing Blackwell (SM100) primitives in TileLang:\r\n\r\n1. **`tcgen05.st` (Register → Tensor Memory Store)**: Enables writing data from registers back into Tensor Memory (TMEM), which is the reverse of the existing `tcgen05.ld`. This is essential for chained GEMM patterns where intermediate results need type conversion (e.g., fp32→bf16) before being fed into the next MMA stage.\r\n\r\n2. **`tcgen05mma_ts` (TMEM-Shared MMA variant)**: Enables GEMM where operand A is read directly from TMEM while operand B comes from shared memory. Combined with `tcgen05.st`, this unlocks the chained GEMM pattern: `SS GEMM → ld → cast → st → TS GEMM`, which is the core building block for Flash Attention on Blackwell.\r\n\r\n### Key Changes\r\n\r\n**New files:**\r\n- `src/tl_templates/cuda/tcgen_05_st.h` — PTX inline assembly templates for all `tcgen05.st` shape variants (32dp32b, 32dp64b, 32dp128b, 32dp256b) with optional `unpack::16b` modifier\r\n- `testing/python/kernel/test_tilelang_kernel_bf16_gemm_tcgen5_ts.py` — Test cases covering SS baseline, chained GEMM (128×128, 256×128), and non-power-of-2 K dimension (K=192)\r\n- `examples/gemm_sm100/gemm_tcgen5mma_ts.py` — Example demonstrating chained MMA: D = (A × B1) × B2\r\n\r\n**Modified files:**\r\n- `src/op/copy.cc` — Extended `LowerTmemCopy` to support `tcgen05.st` direction; **critical fix**: disabled `unpack::16b` for bf16 stores so data is written packed (2 bf16 per 32-bit TMEM column), matching MMA TS's read expectation\r\n- `src/layout/tcgen05_layout.{cc,h}` — Added `getTcgen05MetaSt_*` functions providing Fragment metadata for store operations\r\n- `src/tl_templates/cuda/copy_sm100.h` — Added `tcgen05_st_core` recursive splitting template and wrapper functions for all store shape variants\r\n- `src/op/gemm_py.cc` — Updated `allowTcgen5Mma` to correctly determine `ab_dtype` for TS variant (A from TMEM has accumulator dtype, B from shared has input dtype)\r\n- `tilelang/intrinsics/tcgen05_macro_generator.py` — Added `tcgen05mma_ts` method and `make_mma_store_layout` for TMEM layout inference\r\n- `tilelang/tileop/gemm/gemm_base.py` — Added `is_gemm_ts()` detection and correct `in_dtype` derivation for TS variant\r\n- `tilelang/tileop/gemm/gemm_tcgen05.py` — Added TS variant support in `infer_layout` and `lower`\r\n\r\n### bf16 Pack/Unpack Fix\r\n\r\nThe most critical fix addresses a data corruption issue with bf16 in TMEM:\r\n- **Problem**: `tcgen05.st` was generating `unpack::16b`, which unpacks each uint32 register into 2 separate TMEM columns (128 columns total). But `MMA TS` expects bf16 data *packed* (2 values per column, 64 columns).\r\n- **Solution**: For stores, `unpack::16b` is disabled (`use_pack_unpack_modifier = false`), so 64 uint32 registers (each containing 2 packed bf16) are written directly to 64 TMEM columns. `effective_chunks` still halves correctly for the register count.\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n- [x] SS GEMM bf16 baseline (128×128×128) — verifies tcgen05.ld + cast pipeline\r\n- [x] Chained GEMM 128×128 — full SS → ld → cast → st → TS pipeline\r\n- [x] Chained GEMM 256×128 — larger M dimension (M > block_M)\r\n- [x] Non-power-of-2 K (K=192) — validates `tcgen05_st_core` recursive splitting (192 → 128+64)\r\n- [x] Generated kernel source assertions: confirms `tcgen05mma_ts` and `tcgen05_st` appear in output\r\n- [x] CPU reference computation (avoids cuBLAS issues on Thor/Blackwell environment)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Chained multi-stage GEMM (SS → TS) support and a TS GEMM variant for A-in-tensor-memory + B-in-shared workflows\n  * Expanded tensor-memory store support for 32/64/128/256-bit widths\n\n* **Examples**\n  * New runnable Python example demonstrating chained GEMM scenarios with test entry points and a run utility\n\n* **Tests**\n  * New end-to-end tests validating chained GEMM correctness and emitted kernel components\n\n* **Documentation**\n  * Added docstrings describing TS variant behavior and layout inference\n\n* **Bug Fixes**\n  * More robust tensor-memory copy/store handling and clearer error reporting\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
